.:: Puzzle 3x4-Level-4-16::.
4 different games are played: snooker, mah-jongg, backgammon, canasta
City: marseilles, rome, liverpool, hamburg
There are 4 different nationalities: egyptian, thai, colombian, japanese
1. the person playing snooker is on the left or right of the person playing mah-jongg##3
2. the person traveling to marseilles is in an even position##4
3. the japanese is on the far left##1
4. the person traveling to rome is on the left or right of the person playing canasta##3
5. the person playing mah-jongg is between the thai and the person traveling to liverpool##2
6. the egyptian is the person traveling to hamburg##1
7. the person playing mah-jongg is on the left of the person playing snooker##1
8. the person traveling to marseilles is on the left of the person playing snooker##1

.:: Answer ::.
|             |     1      |    2     |    3    |     4      |
| Game    | backgammon    | mah-jongg     | snooker    | canasta        |
| City       | liverpool   | marseilles | rome | hamburg |
| Nationality   | japanese | colombian      | thai    | egyptian   |

